# Dependencies
#
# Install nginx, node.js, npm, Ruby, sass, bower and grunt-cli
sudo apt-get install ruby
sudo apt-get install nginx
sudo gem install sass
npm install
bower install
# Gedcom Viewer dependency - run once:
# pushd js/lib; rm -rf gedcom-js-viewer; git clone https://github.com/danidin/gedcom-js-viewer.git; popd
# Nginx config - run once:
# sudo cp doc/config/bhs-nginx-site /etc/nginx/sites-available
# Edit the file there to point site root to ./public/index.html and run:
# sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/bhs-nginx-site /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/; sudo service nginx reload

# Configuration files:
vim /etc/bhs/client/config.json

```
{
	"baseUrl":			"api.myjewishidentity.org",
	"auth": 			"auth",
	"user": 			"user",
	"mjs":				"mjs",
	"wizard_search": 	"wsearch",
	"item":				"item",
	"suggest":			"suggest",
	"ftrees_search":	"fsearch",
	"ftrees_get": 		"get_ftree_url",
	"upload": 			"upload"
}
```

vim /etc/bhs/client/config.js

```
angular.module('config', []).
    constant('apiConfig', {
        baseUrl:        '@@baseUrl',
        auth:           '@@auth',
        user:           '@@user', 
        mjs:            '@@mjs', 
        wizard_search:  '@@wizard_search',
        item:           '@@item',
        suggest:        '@@suggest',
        ftrees_search:  '@@ftrees_search',
        ftrees_get:     '@@ftrees_get',
        upload:         '@@upload'
    });
```

grunt build 


# Generate Documentation
The docs had been generated by generator-ngdoc (https://www.npmjs.com/package/generator-ngdoc)
After generation, the (generated) src folder have been removed, since it was not needed.

In order to serve the docs app:

cd docs
gulp docs:serve
& navigate to localhost:3000

Or alternatively, generate your own from the source code.
